\subsection{The [[play]] command}

The [[play]] command uses [[resolve_source]] to handle both
directories and bundle files.
When a bundle is used, [[resolve_source]] creates a temporary
directory that we must clean up---hence the [[finally]] block.

<<typer commands>>=
@app.command()
def play(
    source: Annotated[
        Optional[str],
        typer.Argument(
            help=(
                "Source: directory with .learnlog/ "
                "or a .bundle file. "
                "Defaults to current directory."
            ),
        ),
    ] = None,
    start: Annotated[
        Optional[str],
        typer.Option(
            "--start",
